# Game Design Rules

## Target Audience
- 4-year-old child (Tom)
- Cannot read
- Limited fine motor skills
- Short attention span (5-10 minutes)

## Core Mechanic
- Simple 2D top-down mazes with wide paths
- Joystick/D-pad movement (left stick or arrow keys)
- A button to confirm/interact
- 3-6 decision points per maze maximum

## Design Principles
- NO failure state, NO enemies, NO timers, NO health
- Dead ends have fun surprises (collectibles, animations)
- Wrong turns reward curiosity, never punish
- Gentle hints after 5-8 seconds of inactivity
- Constant positive feedback (sounds, sparkles, praise)
- Every level ends with celebration

## Language Rule
- All in-game dialogue must be in Russian
- Menu text and debug/test text can be in English

## Visual Rules
- Top-down or angled top-down camera
- Wide, readable paths with rounded corners
- Strong contrast between paths and walls
- Large goal object visible from maze sections
- Bright, warm, saturated colors
- No dark shadows or scary spaces

## Audio Rules
- Upbeat, playful background music
- Positive sound effects only
- Short voice lines in Russian
- No buzzers, alarms, or negative sounds

## Maze Structure
- 7 missions across 6 themed zones
- Each mission: intro → pup select → maze → collectibles → goal → celebration
- Progress is horizontal (new scenery, not harder difficulty)
